title.narrative: Programme-funded UK Global Fund Accelerator Programme Advisers

description.narrative: This activity (Programme-funded UK Global Fund Accelerator Programme Advisers) is a component of UK investment in the Global Fund 2020-2022 to reduce transmission and mortality for HIV AIDS, tuberculosis and malaria through treatments, diagnostics and preventive technologies and related services reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Front Line Delivery' and a budget of £2,580,173. This component benefits Africa, regional, and works in the following sector(s): Administrative costs (non-sector allocable). The start date is 01-04-2020 and the end date is 31-03-2023.
